{{Infobox magazine | title = African Business | image_file = African Business cover April 2012.png | editor = Lanre Akinola | category = Business | language = English, French | total_circulation= 25,572<ref>{{cite news|title= Mag ABCs: 137 out 516 consumer mags put on circ year on year, full breakdown|url=http://www.pressgazette.co.uk/just-137-out-516-uk-consumer-magazines-put-sales-year-year-full-breakdown-all-titles|newspaper=[[Press Gazette]]|date=14 February 2013}}</ref> | circulation_year= December 2016 | publisher = IC Publications | founder = Anver Versi | firstdate = January 1982 | frequency = Monthly | country = UK | based = London | website = {{URL|http://africanbusinessmagazine.com/}} | OCLC = 609950292 | issn = 0141-3929 }} '''''African Business''''' is an African business [[magazine]] published by London-based [[IC Publications]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/african-business/oclc/609950292|work=WorldCat|title=African business|accessdate=28 October 2012}}</ref> The current editor is Lanre Akinola.<ref name="TRT_090817">{{cite AV media | people = David Foster (presenter), Jeni Klugman, MD Georgetown Institute for Women, Peace and Security (guest), Shaista Aziz, writer and journalist (guest), Lanre Akinola editor African Business magazine (guest) and Mike Buchanan (guest) | date = 9 August 2017 | accessdate = 16 December 2017 | title= How real is the gender pay gap? | medium= Television | series = [[TRT World#Programmes|The Roundtable]] | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bXUKfohxG3w&list=PLUW304lJeu3Wq792ZuY62Cq7gWzbygo5F | publisher= [[TRT World]] via [[YouTube]]}}</ref>
==History and profile== ''African Business'' was first published in January 1982.<ref>{{cite web|title=African Business|url=https://shop.exacteditions.com/gb/african-business|work=Exact Editions|accessdate=19 November 2016}}</ref> Anver Versi was the founding editor of the magazine.<ref>{{cite news|title=Anver Versi, former Editor, African Business|url=http://africanbusinessmagazine.com/uncategorised/tribute-paid-anver-versi-former-editor-african-business/|accessdate=30 July 2016|work=African Business|date=26 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Anver Versi|url=https://www.oracle.com/webfolder/s/delivery_production/docs/FY14h1/doc2/Anver-Versi.pdf|work=Oracle|accessdate=30 July 2016}}</ref> Its headquarters is in London.<ref>{{cite journal|author=Tokunbo Ojo|title=Framing of the Sino–Africa relationship in diasporic/pan-African news magazines|journal=Chinese Journal of Communication|date=2016|volume=9|issue=1|url=http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/pdf/10.1080/17544750.2015.1049628?needAccess=true|accessdate=8 March 2017}}</ref> The monthly magazine covers business events across Africa. Special reports discuss specific sectors and industries.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://africanbusinessmagazine.com/main-articles/new-african|title=African Business (about)|work=African Business|accessdate=28 October 2012}}</ref> As of 2012, the magazine had about 140,000 subscribers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.exacteditions.com/read/african-business|work=Exact Editions|title=African Business|accessdate=28 October 2012}}</ref> The magazine is published in English and French editions.<ref>{{cite web|ref=harv |url=http://www.africasia.com/index_fr.php |accessdate=28 October 2012|work=IC Publications|title=Accueil}}</ref>
The magazine organizes the annual "African Business Awards" event in collaboration with the [[Commonwealth Business Council]]. The 2011 event was held in [[London]], England.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ic-events.net/awards/african_business_awards_2011/ |title=The African Business Awards London 2011 |accessdate=28 October 2012 |work=IC Publications |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120808235646/http://www.ic-events.net/awards/african_business_awards_2011/ |archivedate=8 August 2012 }}</ref>
