{{Infobox person | name = Luna Shamsuddoha | native_name = লুনা সামসুদ্দোহা | native_name_lang = bn | image = Luna Shamsuddoha at office (3) (cropped).jpg | birth_date = 4 October | birth_place = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] | residence = [[Dhaka]] | nationality = Bangladeshi | known_for = Entrepreneur | education = Masters in International Relations | alma_mater = [[University of Dhaka]] | organization = Bangladesh Women in IT (BWIT) | occupation = IT entrepreneur, Business Leader | title = Chairman of [[Dohatec New Media]] and [[Janata Bank Limited]] | boards = [[Independent University Bangladesh]], [[Janata Bank Limited]], SME Foundation | spouse = A K M Shamsuddoha | parents = Lutfar Rahman (father) and Hasina Rahman (mother) | awards = Bangladesh Business Award (2017), Outstanding Woman in Business (2017), [[Anannya Top Ten Awards]] (2013) }}
'''Luna Shamsuddoha''' (4 October) is a [[Bangladesh|Bangladeshi]] entrepreneur. She is the chairman of the software firm Dohatec New Media, in Dhaka Bangladesh, which she founded in 1992. She is the first woman to head any state-owned in Bangladesh. <ref>{{cite news|title=Luna Shamsuddoha joins state-owned Janata Bank as first ever female chairman|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/business/banks/2018/03/01/luna-shamsuddoha-joins-janata-bank-chairman/|accessdate=2 March 2018|agency=Dhaka Tribune}}</ref> Currently she is the chairman of state-owned [[Janata Bank Limited]]. She is also founder and president of Bangladesh Women in Technology (BWIT).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bwit-bd.com/prof_luna_shamsuddoha.php|title=BWIT|website=www.bwit-bd.com}}</ref> She received the Bangladesh Business Award-2017 for her contribution to the country’s economy and was honored with [[Anannya Top Ten Awards]] for her work in the in local [[software]] industry as a women [[entrepreneur]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.daily-sun.com/printversion/details/224810/Luna-gets-%E2%80%98Bangladesh-Business-Award%E2%80%99 |title=Luna gets ‘Bangladesh Business Award’ |newspaper=The Daily Sun}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.banglanews24.com/business/article/60894/Luna-Shamsuddoha-receives-Bangladesh-Business-Award-2017|title=Luna Shamsuddoha receives Bangladesh Business Award 2017|first=|last=http://www.banglanews24.com|website=www.banglanews24.com}}</ref> She was a board member of SME Foundation, [[Independent University Bangladesh|Independent University Bangladesh (IUB)]], director of state-owned [[Agrani Bank Limited]] and [[Janata Bank Limited]]. She has been featured on global forums on [[technology]], e-Governance and women’s economic participation and empowerment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thewisteriagroup.com/spotlight-on-women-in-business-an-interview-with-dohatecs-luna-shamsuddoha/|title=Spotlight on Women in Business: An Interview with Dohatec's Luna Shamsuddoha|publisher=}}</ref> Luna is a member of Council of Global Thought Leaders on Inclusive Growth, [[Switzerland]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://brac.manthanaward.org/dt_team/luna-shamsuddoha/|title=BRAC - Luna Shamsuddoha|website=brac.manthanaward.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sdasia.co/2015/05/10/innovative-women-entrepreneur-luna-shamsuddoha/|title=Innovative Women Entrepreneur: Luna Shamsuddoha|first=Tasnuba|last=Sinha|date=10 May 2015|publisher=}}</ref> She has joined as chairman of the state-owned [[Janata Bank|Janata Bank Limited]].
==Early life and education== Shamsuddoha was born to Lutfar Rahman and Hasina Rahman on 4 October in [[Dhaka]]. She got her [[Secondary School Certificate|Secondary School Certificate (SSC)]] from [[Viqarunnisa Noon School and College]] and [[Higher Secondary School Certificate|Higher Secondary School Certificate (HSC)]] from [[Holy Cross College, Dhaka|Holy Cross College]]. <ref>{{cite magazine |title=First stated owned bank women chairman of Bangladesh |magazine=Janata Bank Limited bulletin |issue=5th year, 1st issue |publisher=Janata Bank Limited |location=Dhaka |page=3 |language=bn}}</ref> She has a master's degree in International Relations (IR) from [[University of Dhaka]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jb.com.bd/about_us/board_of_directors|title=Janata Bank Board of Directors|last=Wahed|first=Maruf &|website=www.jb.com.bd|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-27}}</ref>
==Career== She began her career as a consultant in 1978 but she started the business in 1985 as the managing partner of The Executive Center. Prior to that, she functioned as an English Language teacher at [[British Council]] Language Resource Center and as a lecturer, English Language, Institute of Modern Languages, [[University of Dhaka]]. Her company is an Independent Software Vendor (ISV) and System Integrator and she works Dohatec since 1992. Dohatec provides software solutions to institutions, government agencies and corporations in the [[United State of America|USA]], [[Canada]], [[Germany]], [[Switzerland]], and Bangladesh. Dohatec’s key clients are the [[World Bank]], [[World Health Organization]], US Postal Service, [[Government of Bangladesh]] and [[Bangladesh Army]]. The company is a Certifying Authority and issues Digital Certificates including identification certificates and SSL Certificates. Luna was a panelist in two sessions of the [[UN]] 59th Commission on the Status of Women and Moderator of UN Online Discussion, UN Women. She participated in UN ITC Trailblazers Summit: Transformations in Sourcing from Women, in São Paulo, [[Brazil]] 2015 – a call for the inclusion of women in public procurement. <ref>{{cite news |title=Local software firms need public patrons to tap into potentials |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/tribune-supplements/business-tribune/2017/08/12/local-software-firms-need-public-patrons-tap-potentials/ |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune}}</ref>
==Personal life== She married to A. K. M. Shamsuddoha, a businessman. The couple has a daughter, Reem Shamsuddoha. <ref>{{cite journal|last1=এই|first1=সময়|title=লুনা শামসুদ্দোহা: দেশের প্রথম রাষ্ট্রায়ত্ত ব্যাংকের নারী চেয়ারম্যান|date=March 4, 2018|volume=৫|issue=৮|page=১৫|language=bn}}</ref>
==Awards== * Bangladesh Business Award, 2017 * Outstanding Woman in Business, 2017 <ref>{{cite news|title=Luna becomes 1st ever woman chairman of state-owned bank|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/business/luna-shamsuddoha-becomes-1st-ever-woman-chairman-state-owned-janata-bank-in-bangladesh-1541551|accessdate=2 March 2018|agency=The Daily Star}}</ref> * Honorary Special Recognition Award by Global Women Inventors & Innovators Network (GWIIN), 2013 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news/luna-shamsuddoha-presented-with-the-gwiin-honorary-award-in-sweden|title=Luna Shamsuddoha presented with the GWIIN Honorary Award in Sweden|date=11 December 2013|publisher=}}</ref> * [[Anannya Top Ten Awards]] (2013)
